In this presidential memorandum, President Barack Obama designates the Secretary of Homeland Security and the Secretary of Defense as rotating Chairpersons of the Defense Production Act Committee. The Chairperson will rotate annually on April 1, with the Secretary of Homeland Security initially serving as Chairperson for the remainder of the first term. The Secretary of Homeland Security and the Secretary of Defense are instructed to establish responsibilities for funding and administrative support through an interagency agreement. The Chairperson is also directed to invite all Members of the Committee to each meeting and ensure compliance with reporting requirements. The Secretary of Homeland Security is authorized to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.